  • Classes in https.gl_immunogenomics_org.gl_resource used by https.gl_immunogenomics_org.gl_resource 
    Class and Description
    Allele
    An allele describes variation at a particular locus.
    AlleleList
    An allele list is an unordered collection of one or more alleles representing alleleic ambiguity separated in GL String format by the character '/'.
    AlleleList.Alleles
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    Genotype
    A genotype is an unordered collection of one or more haplotypes separated in GL String format by the character '+'.
    Genotype.Haplotypes
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    GenotypeList
    A genotype list is an unordered collection of one or more genotypes representing genotypic ambiguity separated in GL String format by the character '|'.
    GenotypeList.Genotypes
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    GlResource
    Abstract class for all resources representable in GL String format.
    Haplotype
    A haplotype is an unordered collection of one or more allele lists in phase separated in GL String format by the character '~'.
    Haplotype.AlleleLists
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    Locus
    A locus identifies a genomic location at which alleles may be defined.
    MultilocusUnphasedGenotype
    A multilocus unphased genotype is an unordered collection of one or more genotype lists separated in GL String format by the character '^'.
    MultilocusUnphasedGenotype.GenotypeLists
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
